{"title":"Park Tool releases new derailleur hanger gauge, bit tool and more","link":"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/park-tool-releases-dag-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-qth-1-bit-tool-and-more/","date":1615215671000,"content":"<p>The world’s largest bicycle tool company, <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/tag/park-tool/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Park Tool</a>, has been busy expanding its enormous catalogue of tools. Today the company has announced four new additions to the workshop range which arrive hot on the heels of a recent expansion in bearing-related tools.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The DAG-3: A new derailleur hanger alignment tool</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2016/08/best-bicycle-derailleur-hanger-tool/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Derailleur hanger alignment gauges</a> are a must-have tool in any professional workshop or well-equipped home setup. Park Tool’s DAG-2 series of derailleur hanger alignment gauges have been widely copied in recent decades and have gone through a number of iterations in order to keep up to date with frame compatibility and the demand for increased alignment accuracy.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While Park’s industrial-looking DAG-2.2 remains a staple in many workshops around the world, the likes of EVT (Efficient Velo Technology) and Abbey Bike Tools have shown that there are more elegant and faster ways to measure the straightness of a derailleur hanger. Notably, these tools allow the sliding indicator to quickly pivot around frame obstructions, fender struts, and racks without changing the measurement setting.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new DAG-3 is Park Tool’s answer to these innovations and offers a pivoting indicator to speed up the process. This workshop tool is designed to work with everything from 16&#8243; to 29&#8243; wheels, and offers a low-profile head to fit low-clearance thru-axle derailleur hangers. The main body is aluminium and offers a keyed channel for the sliding indicator component. That sliding indicator simply uses a friction fit without the ability to lock it in place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First impressions are that the threaded tip of the tool is noticeably well toleranced and doesn&#8217;t wiggle like previous versions of the DAG-2, while the aluminium construction provides a lighter and more refined feel in use. Priced at US$117, the new DAG-3 is a premium upgrade to the pre-existing DAG-2.2 (US$80). Expect an update to the “<a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2016/08/best-bicycle-derailleur-hanger-tool/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">best derailleur hanger tool</a>” article in the near future.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped wp-block-gallery__slider\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-7-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"488791\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-7.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=488791\" class=\"wp-image-488791\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-7-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-7-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-7-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-7-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-7-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-7.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The new DAG-3 allows the indicator to flip 90º for quicker use. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-8-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"488794\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-8.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=488794\" class=\"wp-image-488794\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-8-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-8-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-8-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-8-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-8-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-8.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">With the indicator flipped out and ready for measurement. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-news-cyclingtips-5-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"488788\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-gauge-n